360, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0865216544688394e-21, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Securing 14 golds, 22 silvers and 29 bronze medals overall, the Brits actually beat their target of 50 on Day 12 of the Games.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite exceeding their goals, Team GB's gold medal total is their lowest since they returned just nine at the 2004 Olympics in Athens.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0865216544688394e-21, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.659670251282939e-28, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain's highest gold medal total was 29 in 2012, while65 medals were won in total in London.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999354567887946, \"rank\": 3.5717455166542576e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999090505, \"rank\": 9.111949465686125e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"],